data.title: Etymology of quetzal by etymonline
data.meta_description: "tail-feather." The full bird name in Nahuatl was quetzaltototl, with tototl "bird." See origin and meaning of quetzal.
data.text: magnificent bird of Central America with brilliant plumage, 1827, from Spanish quetzal, from Nahuatl (Aztecan) quetzalli, "tail-feather." The full bird name in Nahuatl was quetzaltototl, with tototl "bird."
